WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:05.005
-[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

00:13.448 --> 00:16.886
-♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

00:17.017 --> 00:20.585
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

00:20.716 --> 00:24.633
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HAVE SOMEBODY ♪

00:24.763 --> 00:28.028
♪ ON THE EDGE
OF SURRENDERS INSIDE ♪

00:28.158 --> 00:30.813
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY

00:31.466 --> 00:34.947
♪ IT'S GONNA BE ALL RIGHT ♪

00:36.993 --> 00:38.864
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

00:38.995 --> 00:42.346
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

00:45.306 --> 00:49.397
-♪ I'LL BE READY
-♪ I'LL BE READY

00:49.527 --> 00:51.573
♪ WHENEVER YOU FEAR

00:51.703 --> 00:53.401
♪ OH, DON'T YOU FEAR

00:53.531 --> 00:56.534
♪ I'LL BE READY

00:56.665 --> 00:59.842
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

00:59.972 --> 01:03.280
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

01:20.776 --> 01:22.647
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

01:22.778 --> 01:26.086
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

01:27.826 --> 01:31.743
♪ NO! I'LL BE READY

01:31.874 --> 01:35.486
♪ I'LL BE READY
WHENEVER YOU FEAR ♪

01:35.617 --> 01:37.227
♪ OH, DON'T YOU FEAR

01:37.358 --> 01:40.752
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:40.883 --> 01:43.886
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:44.016 --> 01:47.107
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

02:17.746 --> 02:20.140
-[CHEERING]

02:25.623 --> 02:27.538
-LET'S GO RIGHT NOW.
I'M WALKING OUT OF HERE.

02:27.669 --> 02:29.758
-WHAT ABOUT YOUR CHIPS?

02:29.888 --> 02:32.021
-WILL YOU CASH ME OUT?
-CERTAINLY.

02:33.457 --> 02:35.155
-YOU WERE WONDERFUL.
-THANK YOU.

02:35.764 --> 02:39.159
-SO WERE YOU, MY LUCKY CHARM.
-AND WHAT DO I GET?

02:39.898 --> 02:41.248
-WHAT ABOUT THIS?

02:59.048 --> 03:00.441
-WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED?

03:01.355 --> 03:02.878
-I GOT SHOT.

03:03.705 --> 03:05.533
-IT'S A PRETTY BAD WOUND.

03:05.663 --> 03:09.058
-HANG ON.
-WHAT? [GASPING]

03:12.322 --> 03:15.978
OW! OW!
-I KNOW IT HURTS.
JUST HOLD STILL.

03:16.108 --> 03:20.504
-PLEASE, TAKE IT EASY.
-OKAY. OKAY.

03:23.290 --> 03:25.466
HANG ON, HANG ON.

03:36.607 --> 03:40.307
-[GASPS] THERE YOU ARE, YOU
LITTLE DEVIL. COME BACK HERE.
-WHOA!

03:40.437 --> 03:42.831
-LOOK OUT, MAN COMING THROUGH.
MAN IN TROUBLE, COMING THROUGH.
LOOK OUT.

03:42.961 --> 03:45.225
COMING THROUGH. LOOK OUT.
MAN IN TROUBLE, COMING THROUGH.

04:00.501 --> 04:02.242
-ARE YOU OKAY?
-YEAH.

04:03.155 --> 04:04.853
I'M JUST COMING DOWN
FROM THE RUSH.

04:06.071 --> 04:08.030
-NOT TOO FAR DOWN, I HOPE.

04:10.598 --> 04:13.427
-MATTHEW, I DIDN'T COME HERE

04:13.557 --> 04:15.167
FOR THE REASON YOU THINK.

04:16.908 --> 04:18.345
-THEN WHAT WAS THAT KISS
ALL ABOUT?

04:20.869 --> 04:23.785
I THOUGHT WE MEANT SOMETHING
TO EACH OTHER, CJ.

04:23.915 --> 04:25.830
OR ARE WE STILL PLAYING GAMES?

04:27.963 --> 04:29.965
-THIS ISN'T A GAME, MATTHEW.

04:30.095 --> 04:32.010
I MEAN, YOU MIGHT FIND THIS HARD
TO UNDERSTAND,

04:32.141 --> 04:34.622
BUT YOU KNOW,
I GREW UP IN VEGAS.

04:36.885 --> 04:39.931
MY GRANDFATHER WAS A DEALER
IN A CASINO.

04:40.802 --> 04:44.458
I MEAN, I'VE BEEN PLAYING
BLACKJACK WITH HIM SINCE AS
FAR BACK AS I CAN REMEMBER.

04:45.676 --> 04:48.723
HE TAUGHT ME HOW TO COUNT CARDS,
READ THE DEALER,

04:48.853 --> 04:50.159
PLAY THE PERCENTAGES.

04:52.727 --> 04:55.338
AND BY THE TIME I WAS 15,
I KNEW EVERY TRICK IN THE BOOK.

04:56.078 --> 04:58.341
BY THE TIME I WAS 19,
I WAS OUT OF CONTROL.

04:59.429 --> 05:01.779
I WON AND LOST A SMALL FORTUNE

05:02.258 --> 05:04.478
BEFORE I REALIZED I HAD
A GAMBLING PROBLEM.

05:07.132 --> 05:08.482
-I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY.

05:09.657 --> 05:12.094
-IT'S JUST THAT IT HAD
BEEN FIVE YEARS

05:12.224 --> 05:13.878
SINCE I SET FOOT IN A CASINO.

05:15.619 --> 05:17.534
I REALLY THOUGHT I'D GOTTEN
THAT OUT OF MY SYSTEM.

05:17.665 --> 05:20.232
-HEY, WHO SAID YOU DIDN'T?

05:21.321 --> 05:23.453
YOU HAD A LUCKY STREAK,
AND YOU WALKED AWAY.

05:23.584 --> 05:24.889
JUST DON'T GO BACK.

05:26.935 --> 05:28.850
-IT'S A LOT MORE COMPLICATED
THAN THAT.

05:34.943 --> 05:36.466
I JUST DON'T TRUST MYSELF
ANYMORE.

05:37.162 --> 05:40.470
-THEN TRUST ME.
I WON'T LET YOU OUT OF MY SIGHT.

05:43.734 --> 05:45.170
-CAN YOU DO ME A FAVOR, MATTHEW?

05:45.301 --> 05:47.477
-MM-HMM.
-WILL YOU JUST HOLD ME?

05:53.178 --> 05:57.357
-[THUNDER CRASHING]

05:58.575 --> 06:00.142
-ARE YOU STILL MAD AT ME?

06:00.272 --> 06:02.187
-NO, I'M NOT MAD AT YOU.

06:02.318 --> 06:04.799
-YES, YOU ARE.
-NO, I'M NOT!

06:06.148 --> 06:08.498
I WAS THE ONE WHO WANTED US
TO SPEND THE NIGHT TOGETHER.

06:09.369 --> 06:11.762
-YEAH, WELL,
THIS MIGHT BE OUR LAST ONE,

06:11.893 --> 06:14.765
SO WE MIGHT
AS WELL ENJOY IT, YOU KNOW?

06:17.028 --> 06:19.379
-WE CAN'T BE TOO FAR
FROM A SHIPPING LANE.

06:20.684 --> 06:22.730
WE JUST GOT TO HANG ON.

06:22.860 --> 06:26.516
ONCE IT'S LIGHT,
THEY'LL SPOT US.

06:29.867 --> 06:32.783
-DO YOU THINK YOU CAN LAST
ALL NIGHT?

06:33.741 --> 06:36.091
-ARE YOU KIDDING? HA HA!

06:36.221 --> 06:38.789
YOU'LL STARVE BEFORE YOU DROWN.

06:38.920 --> 06:40.922
-[LAUGHING]

06:45.230 --> 06:48.451
-[KNOCK ON DOOR]

06:57.634 --> 06:58.983
-NOBODY KNOWS
THEY WENT OVERBOARD.

06:59.114 --> 07:01.029
IT'S BUSINESS AS USUAL
ON ALL DECKS.

07:01.159 --> 07:04.467
-FOR NOW. WHAT HAPPENS WHEN
THEY'RE REPORTED MISSING?

07:07.644 --> 07:09.167
THE GIRL SAW US.

07:11.518 --> 07:13.389
-THEY'LL NEVER SURVIVE
IN THESE WATERS.

07:17.175 --> 07:20.918
-[THUNDER CRASHING]

07:21.049 --> 07:21.919
-MITCH.

07:23.747 --> 07:24.574
-YEAH.

07:25.357 --> 07:27.534
-SOME VACATION, HUH?

07:27.664 --> 07:32.756
-[LAUGHS] IT DOESN'T GET
MUCH BETTER THAN THIS!

07:32.887 --> 07:35.324
-[COUGHS]

08:48.615 --> 08:50.442
-HI.
-HI. COULDN'T STAY AWAY?

08:50.573 --> 08:52.227
-WELL, WHEN YOU'RE HOT,
YOU'RE HOT.

08:53.097 --> 08:54.621
-GIVE THE LADY HER $20,000.

08:55.970 --> 08:58.581
AND A CHIP FOR GOOD LUCK.
-THANK YOU.

09:08.983 --> 09:12.334
-BLACKJACK. PICKING UP RIGHT
FROM WHERE YOU LEFT OFF.

09:19.863 --> 09:22.213
DOUBLE?
-YEAH.

09:34.965 --> 09:36.097
OKAY.

09:38.882 --> 09:42.016
-[COUGHING, GASPING]

11:06.753 --> 11:08.493
-[SIGHS]

11:15.109 --> 11:17.241
-MITCH! MITCH!

11:19.591 --> 11:22.638
MITCH.
-STEPHANIE. STEPHANIE!

11:22.769 --> 11:27.077
-MITCH. MITCH!

11:27.817 --> 11:30.211
-HANG ON. HANG ON!

11:31.995 --> 11:34.650
-HANG ON. HANG ON.
-[COUGHING]

12:41.282 --> 12:42.544
-CJ.

12:44.328 --> 12:46.069
-HI, MATTHEW.

12:46.200 --> 12:47.810
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING OUT HERE?

12:54.774 --> 12:56.427
-I SAW A BIRD.

12:59.343 --> 13:00.431
LAND.

13:04.958 --> 13:05.828
LOOK!

13:10.006 --> 13:13.401
-IT'S A MIRAGE, MITCH.
-NO, IT'S NOT.

13:14.445 --> 13:15.795
IT'S A MIRACLE.

13:19.494 --> 13:22.758
-OH, MY GOD. WE MADE IT.

13:22.889 --> 13:26.066
OH, MITCH, WE'RE SAVED.

13:33.377 --> 13:35.466
OH, MY GOD! MITCH.

13:45.607 --> 13:47.130
-HOW MUCH DID YOU LOSE?

13:49.219 --> 13:50.220
EVERYTHING?

13:51.700 --> 13:54.659
HEY, LOOK AT IT THIS WAY,
AT LEAST YOU WERE PLAYING
WITH THEIR MONEY.

13:55.399 --> 13:58.185
-YEAH, UNTIL I GOT A $5,000
LINE OF CREDIT.

13:59.229 --> 14:01.492
-YOU'RE DOWN 5 GRAND?

14:02.754 --> 14:05.409
-LISTEN, MATTHEW,
IT'S NOT YOUR PROBLEM.
I'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

14:05.540 --> 14:08.325
-HOW? WHAT ARE YOU
GOING TO DO, CJ?

14:08.456 --> 14:10.545
WHAT, ARE YOU GOING TO
WASH DISHES FOR THE REST
OF THE CRUISE?

14:11.067 --> 14:14.157
-WELL, WHAT DO YOU SUGGEST I DO?
-LET ME BAIL YOU OUT.

14:14.288 --> 14:15.811
-HOW?

14:15.942 --> 14:18.901
-WITH MY CREDIT CARD.
IT CAN HOLD THAT MUCH.

14:19.032 --> 14:20.729
-NO, THANK YOU.

14:20.860 --> 14:23.558
-LOOK, IF YOU WERE IN THE
NEXT TOWER AND I NEEDED BACKUP,

14:23.688 --> 14:26.604
YOU'D BE THERE, WOULDN'T YOU?
-IT'S NOT THE SAME THING.

14:26.735 --> 14:28.389
-THEN HOW'S IT DIFFERENT?

14:37.311 --> 14:40.183
-DON'T MOVE. DON'T MOVE.

14:42.925 --> 14:45.232
BET YOU'RE NOT THINKING
ABOUT YOUR EX-HUSBAND NOW.

14:45.754 --> 14:46.886
-AS A MATTER OF FACT, I AM.

14:48.975 --> 14:52.065
HE'S THE SOLE BENEFICIARY
OF MY LIFE INSURANCE POLICY.

14:52.195 --> 14:54.067
I NEVER GOT AROUND
TO CHANGING MY WILL.

14:59.986 --> 15:01.639
-WELL, WE'RE NOT DEAD YET.

15:02.162 --> 15:04.773
-THEN WHY IS MY LIFE
FLASHING BEFORE MY EYES?

15:08.385 --> 15:11.258
[PANTING]

15:44.813 --> 15:45.727
I LOVE YOU.

15:47.250 --> 15:49.818
I ALWAYS HAVE,
FROM THE MOMENT I MET YOU.

15:52.081 --> 15:52.995
[SCREAMING]

16:21.632 --> 16:23.547
-[GRUNTS]

16:27.116 --> 16:28.291
COME ON!

16:45.700 --> 16:47.571
-MITCH, YOU DID IT!

16:47.702 --> 16:49.182
HE'S GOING AWAY.

16:50.009 --> 16:51.010
-COME ON,

16:51.749 --> 16:54.970
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE
BEFORE HE TELLS HIS BIG BROTHER.

16:56.232 --> 16:57.320
COME ON.

17:06.068 --> 17:08.201
-GOOD MORNING.
-BOTH: MORNING. MORNING.

17:08.983 --> 17:10.029
-IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

17:10.942 --> 17:12.509
-EVERYTHING'S FINE.

17:13.205 --> 17:15.251
-HAVE EITHER OF YOU SEEN MITCH
OR STEPHANIE?

17:15.859 --> 17:17.862
-HAVE YOU CHECKED HIS ROOM?
-YEAH.

17:17.992 --> 17:19.907
-THEY PROBABLY DON'T WANT
TO BE DISTURBED.

17:21.300 --> 17:22.998
THEY'RE HAVING A LITTLE
ON-BOARD ROMANCE.

17:23.128 --> 17:24.478
-OH.

17:28.395 --> 17:29.918
-I WANT A SHOWER.

17:49.285 --> 17:52.941
-I'VE CHECKED BOTH THEIR ROOMS,
THE POOL, THE BREAKFAST BUFFET
AND THE WEIGHT ROOM.

17:53.072 --> 17:56.858
OKAY, I'M REALLY GETTING
NERVOUS NOW. SOMETHING'S
GOING ON.

17:56.988 --> 17:58.686
-WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

17:58.816 --> 18:01.210
-LOOK, I THINK THERE'S AN
ESCAPED CONVICT ON THE SHIP.

18:02.559 --> 18:04.344
-WHAT?

18:04.474 --> 18:06.563
-I DON'T KNOW IF IT HAS ANYTHING
TO DO WITH STEPHANIE AND MITCH,

18:06.694 --> 18:08.609
BUT THE GUY IN THE ROOM NEXT
TO ME, HE LOOKS JUST LIKE--

18:08.739 --> 18:10.654
-HEY!
HAVE ANY OF YOU SEEN MITCH?

18:11.481 --> 18:13.483
-NO. OR STEPHANIE.

18:13.614 --> 18:16.007
-WHY? WHAT'S WRONG?
AND WHAT HAVE YOU GOT THERE?

18:16.138 --> 18:18.532
-MITCH'S JACKET. YOU KNOW,
I FOUND IT OVER THERE
BY THE RAILING.

18:18.662 --> 18:21.230
THIS IS NOT AN ITEM THAT MITCH
WOULD CASUALLY TOSS ASIDE.

18:21.361 --> 18:22.275
I MEAN, FEEL THIS MATERIAL.

18:24.668 --> 18:26.192
-DO YOU GUYS THINK SOMETHING
HAPPENED TO THEM?

18:29.978 --> 18:31.284
-I THINK WE BETTER FIND OUT.

18:38.073 --> 18:40.728
-[COUGHING]

18:41.381 --> 18:43.861
MITCH! ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

18:43.992 --> 18:46.429
-MY ARMS FEEL LIKE ANCHORS.

18:47.778 --> 18:49.563
-WHERE DO YOU THINK WE ARE?

18:52.305 --> 18:53.393
-AUSTRALIA.

18:55.090 --> 18:57.658
-THERE'S A STRING
OF UNINHABITED ISLANDS

18:57.788 --> 18:59.312
OFF THE COAST OF BAJA.

18:59.442 --> 19:01.227
-HOW FAR OFF THE COAST?

19:03.925 --> 19:05.318
-THREE-HUNDRED MILES.

19:06.406 --> 19:08.016
-THREE-HUNDRED MILES?

19:21.638 --> 19:22.770
-AT THIS POINT,
THAT'S ALL WE KNOW.

19:22.900 --> 19:24.685
YES, I WILL. ROGER AND OUT.

19:27.122 --> 19:28.776
I'VE JUST ALERTED
THE U.S. COAST GUARD.

19:28.906 --> 19:31.300
-EVERYONE ON BOARD'S BEEN
ACCOUNTED FOR EXCEPT MITCH,

19:31.431 --> 19:33.737
STEPHANIE AND ANOTHER PASSENGER
NAMED CARL FRANKS.

19:35.043 --> 19:37.480
-SIR, I THINK THERE'S A PRETTY
FAIR CHANCE THEY WENT OVERBOARD.

19:37.611 --> 19:39.743
-YES, BUT WHEN AND WHERE?

19:41.005 --> 19:42.398
THE NAVIGATIONAL CHARTS.

19:43.138 --> 19:45.445
-CAPTAIN, YOU'RE NOT THINKING
OF TURNING THE SHIP AROUND.

19:46.054 --> 19:47.098
-THESE PEOPLE RESCUED
MY DAUGHTER.

19:48.187 --> 19:50.276
I'LL DO EVERYTHING IN MY POWER
TO FIND THEM.

19:50.928 --> 19:52.060
-YES, SIR.

19:52.191 --> 19:54.149
-WE'RE RE-ADJUSTING THE COURSE.

19:54.280 --> 19:57.631
TAKE THOSE BINOCULARS AND START
SEARCHING BOTH PORT
AND STARBOARD.

19:57.761 --> 20:01.374
WE PASSED ALONG THE EDGE
OF A MAJOR TROPICAL STORM.
THEY COULD BE ANYWHERE.

20:08.859 --> 20:11.732
-[KNOCK ON DOOR]

20:16.215 --> 20:18.652
-THEY'RE GOING BACK FOR THEM.
-WHAT?

20:19.348 --> 20:21.089
-YOU CAN FEEL IT ALREADY.
THE SHIP'S TURNING AROUND.

20:24.266 --> 20:27.530
-WE'VE GOT TO GET TO CABO
BY NOON. THAT TRAWLER
WON'T WAIT.

20:36.409 --> 20:39.063
-FULL SPEED AHEAD.
STEADY AS SHE GOES.

20:39.890 --> 20:41.327
GIVE ME A READING
ON THE STARBOARD COMPASS.

20:50.684 --> 20:52.163
-[DOOR OPENS]

20:56.298 --> 20:57.821
-EVERYBODY,
STAY RIGHT WHERE YOU ARE.

20:58.692 --> 21:00.215
RIGHT WHERE YOU ARE.

21:06.830 --> 21:08.571
NOW YOU,

21:08.702 --> 21:11.444
PUT THIS SHIP BACK
ON COURSE TO CABO SAN LUCAS.

21:11.574 --> 21:15.970
-AND IF I REFUSE?
-IF YOU REFUSE?

21:17.537 --> 21:20.888
IF YOU REFUSE,
PEOPLE WILL DIE,

21:21.018 --> 21:22.977
STARTING WITH HER.

21:27.068 --> 21:28.461
-WE STOPPED.

21:28.591 --> 21:30.550
-MAYBE SOMEBODY SPOTTED
MITCH AND STEPHANIE.

21:30.680 --> 21:32.421
-YEAH, WELL, KEEP LOOKING.
I'LL GO SEE WHAT'S UP.

21:32.552 --> 21:36.033
-AMY, THE SHIP HAS BEEN
COMMANDEERED BY TERRORISTS.

21:36.164 --> 21:38.209
THEY'RE THREATENING
TO KILL YOUR FRIEND.

21:44.477 --> 21:46.957
-THE BRIDGE IS SECURE.
-OKAY, GET THESE PEOPLE TIED UP.

21:47.741 --> 21:49.308
-SIT DOWN.

21:49.438 --> 21:52.398
-MAN: MOTOR VESSEL "SOUTHWARD,"
MOTOR VESSEL SOUTHWARD.

21:52.528 --> 21:56.793
THIS IS COAST GUARD RESCUE 6565
ON CHANNEL 16.

21:56.924 --> 21:59.622
SOUTHWARD, CAN YOU UPDATE US
ON YOUR SITUATION?

21:59.753 --> 22:01.320
-IF I DON'T RESPOND--
-SHUT UP.

22:02.190 --> 22:03.322
LET ME THINK FOR A SECOND.

22:07.500 --> 22:10.938
-I'LL SAY THE EMERGENCY HAS BEEN
CANCELLED, AND WE'RE PROCEEDING
TO MEXICO AS PLANNED.

22:11.068 --> 22:14.463
-NO, YOU WILL TELL THEM YOU HAVE
AN EMERGENCY EVACUATION.

22:14.594 --> 22:18.685
-MOTOR VESSEL SOUTHWARD,
COAST GUARD RESCUE 6565.

22:18.815 --> 22:22.079
DO YOU READ ME ON CHANNEL 16?
I'D LIKE TO SPEAK
TO YOUR CAPTAIN.

22:22.210 --> 22:23.994
OVER.
-GET ON THE HORN.

22:29.260 --> 22:30.784
IT'S THE BEST WAY OUT.

22:45.494 --> 22:46.582
-OKAY.

22:50.499 --> 22:52.414
-[STAMMERING]
M-MITCH, I'M FREEZING.

22:52.545 --> 22:55.678
-I KNOW. I'LL HAVE A FIRE
STARTED HERE IN A SECOND.

23:03.120 --> 23:05.862
-MY HANDS ARE LIKE ICE.

23:08.952 --> 23:10.258
HYPOTHERMIA.

23:15.132 --> 23:16.177
MY BODY...

23:16.307 --> 23:18.440
TEMPERATURE'S DROPPING.

23:19.180 --> 23:22.183
-COME ON. COME ON.

23:25.099 --> 23:27.493
[BLOWING]

23:27.623 --> 23:29.843
COME ON. COME ON.

23:42.725 --> 23:45.641
STEPHANIE. STEPHANIE.

24:03.920 --> 24:08.708
♪ USED RUN WILD AND FREE
WITH FAITH LIKE A CHILD ♪

24:08.838 --> 24:12.320
♪ ALWAYS BELIEVED I WAS SOMEONE

24:13.626 --> 24:17.891
♪ FACE MY FEARS AND LEAVE THEM BEHIND

24:18.021 --> 24:21.721
♪ NEVER COMPROMISE FOR NO-ONE

24:22.983 --> 24:26.334
♪ THAT'S WHAT IT MEANS TO BELIEVE

24:27.640 --> 24:31.034
♪ TO TRUST IN SOMETHING YOU CAN'T SEE

24:31.165 --> 24:35.735
♪ HEAVENS NOT TOO FAR AWAY

